# Fork-Only Development

This checkout is a personal fork of the upstream LinkedIn MCP server.

## Hard Rules

- NEVER create pull requests targeting the upstream source repository.
- Keep local feature work in the personal fork and merge there.
- Treat upstream as a read-only source for periodic sync and review only.
- Do not depend on upstream accepting local job-hunt or application-flow changes.

## Sync Discipline

- Use `runx git fetch --repo linkedin-mcp` to refresh fork state.
- Use fork-local branches and PRs for all changes.
- Before deleting a branch, verify it is merged in the fork.
